  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `2021.03.02-alpha`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nCalling `eth_estimateGas` with two arguments (the second being the block number or hash) should estimate gas against the specified block as per https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/2586.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nCalling `eth_estimateGas` with two arguments results in the following error:\r\n\r\n```too many arguments, want at most 1``` \r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nCall `eth_estimateGas` with a block number or hash as the second argument as per the console binding added in geth at https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/commit/c1544423d655f540b55bb6ec0e7167dad9683c42.\r\n",
